'''OOAK''' stands for "one of a kind", an acronym that is widely used on the [[Internet]] by artists who make original items such as [[jewelry]], [[fashion_doll | fashion dolls]], [[reborn_doll | reborn baby dolls]], weapons, sculptures, and clothing. 

{{vocab-stub}}
In the doll-collecting arena OOAK dolls sculpted by renowned artists, such as Floyd Bell, Lorna Miller-Sands, and Laura Tuzio-Ross are highly collectible.  Bell's medium of choice is wood.  His wood-carved dolls focus on historical African Americans, children and babies.  Miller-Sands' and Tuzio-Ross both create life-like babies and children using various clays and silicone.  All three artists enjoy a huge following of collectors who delight in owning their one-of-a-kind creations.